</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName genus="Aleopcosa" lsidName="Aleopcosa" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="genus">Aleopcosa</taxonomicName>
is a large genus of wolf spiders with currently 161 desribed species that are distributed in Eurasia (75% of species), and a few (9%) with a Holarctic or Palearctic distribution (Blagoev &amp; Dondale 2014). Only seven species occur in South America (Venezuela, Ecuador and Argentina) and probably do not belong to that genus but we retain this species in 
<taxonomicName genus="Alopectosa" lsidName="Alopectosa" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="genus">Alopectosa</taxonomicName>
, emphasizing the need for revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
